[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/process-engine-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/process-engine-6-7)

**File:** task.ipd

**Shows:** Task Element, Usage of Doxee Workplace human tasks

**Components:** Start Element, Mapping Element, Task Element, End Element

This process shows the basic usage of a Task Element which creates a human task in Doxee Workplace. It contains a Task Element of type "approval-task.ht", which creates a human task for reviewing documents and approving or declining them. The Mapping Element which comes before, defines the ids and labels for the workflow steps, which usually represent the tasks in the process. They are passed to the task along with the id of the current workflow step, so the human task can display them. The task provides the approval result, a comment and a direction text for defining the further process path as outputs. For more information regarding the inputs and outputs of human tasks please consult the Doxee Workplace documentation.
